cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes buffer-aided physical-layer network coding techniques, which are closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with cooperative direct-sequence code-division multiple access systems, which are part of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The relay pair selection algorithm used in the proposed techniques can be seen as a control system, which falls under systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed techniques can be used for multimedia transmission, as they aim to improve the performance of data transmission. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not directly related to cryptography and security, the paper's focus on improving the performance of data transmission can indirectly contribute to enhancing the security of communication systems.
